**Damage Report:**

**Vehicle Make/Model:** Not specified (based on the image provided)

**Location of Damage:**
- The damage is located on the rear fender of the vehicle, near the taillight.

**Type of Damage:**
- The damage appears to be a small dent or indentation in the paintwork. There is also some visible scratching around the area, suggesting that the impact was not severe but has caused minor surface damage.

**Additional Notes:**
- The dent is relatively small and localized.
- There are no signs of significant structural damage to the fender or any other part of the vehicle.
- The surrounding paint seems to have been affected by the impact, indicating that the dent may have caused some minor paint damage as well.

**Recommendation:**
- The damage can likely be repaired with a touch-up paint job to address the scratches and minor dent.
- It is advisable to have a professional assess the extent of the damage before proceeding with repairs to ensure all areas are properly addressed.

If you need further information or if there is more extensive damage, please provide additional images or details.
